node.title: Cataloochee Creek
node.description: Really liked the interesting configuration of this tree which extends over Cataloochee Creek.

node.title: The young bull emerges
node.description: One of the young bulls in Cataloochee emerges from the woods during dusk.

node.title: Reflections of Fall
node.description: Pools of color along the Chinnabee Silent Trail near Cheaha State Park.

node.title: It's Natural
node.description: Rarely in nature do you see such a wide, straight drop.  I'm not sure if this fall has a name or not.  It's located just beyond the horse camp on Cataloochee Creek in GSMNP. Hit "L" to view on black.

node.title: Stalking Breakfast
node.description: A heron patiently waits for his breakfast in a marsh at Gulf State Park.

node.title: First Light
node.description: Long exposure shot from underneath the Gulf Shores pier just before sunrise.  No saturation adjustment.  The eerie lighting is a combination of the "environmentally safe" lamps and creeping sunlight.  Please hit "L" to view on black.

node.title: Cataloochee Meadows in the Fog
node.description: Type "L" to view in the lightbox.
